{
  "texts": [
    "Helping in forming a differential diagnosisOne of the most important skills for medical graduates is the capacity to generate a differential diagnosis for a particular clinical presentation [69].",
    "According to studies, generative AI chatbots such as GPT-3 and GPT-4 can generate high-accuracy differential-diagnosis lists for common chief complaints, with correct diagnosis rates of up to 93.3% in common cases [70], however their performance drops with uncommon presentations [71].",
    "A meta-analysis of 54 studies that generative AI models had an overall diagnosis accuracy of 56.9%, with considerable variations across 17 medical specialties [72].",
    "The study found that while expert physicians still outperform AI in diagnosis accuracy, some generative AI models, such as Prometheus (Bing) and GPT-4, perform comparably to non-expert physicians in certain specialties.",
    "In another study, a retrospective analysis of 100 patient records, ChatGPT-4 displayed proficiency in detecting specific conditions such as coxarthrosis and gonarthrosis, consistently aligning with clinical judgments reached by orthopedic practitioners [73]."
  ]
}